OL,3,CGovernment's flagship welfare bill at
OL,4,Crisk ahead of crunch vote next week
OL,6,FThe amendment, which ITV News has
OL,7,Fseen, heavily criticises the
OL,8,Fgovernment's implementation of this
OL,9,Fbill and reads: "This house, whilst
OL,10,Fnoting the need for the reform of the
OL,11,Fsocial security system, and agreeing
OL,12,Fwith the Government's principles for
OL,13,Fproviding support to people into work
OL,14,Fand protecting people who cannot work,
OL,15,Fdeclines to give a Second Reading to
OL,16,Fthe 'Universal Credit and Personal
OL,17,FIndependent Payment' Bill because its
OL,18,Fprovisions have not been subject to a
OL,19,Fformal consultation with disabled
OL,20,Fpeople, or co-produced with them, or
OL,21,Ftheir carers."
